GROUP_BY CLASS: Grouping the results from a TABLE

In a table,  need sum of sal of employee, who belongs to each department.

	 SELECT DEPARTMENT_ID SUM(SALARY) FROM employee; // sum of salary of whole TABLE
	 
	 SELECT DEPARTMENT_ID,SUM(SALARY) FROM employee GROUP BY DEPARTMENT_ID; // sum of salary for specific DEPARTMENT
	 
	 SELECT DEPARTMENT_ID,AVG(SALARY) FROM employee GROUP BY DEPARTMENT_ID; // AVG of salary for specific DEPARTMENT
	 
	  SELECT DEPARTMENT_ID,MAX(SALARY), MIN(SALARY), FROM employee GROUP BY DEPARTMENT_ID; //max and min sal of department
	  
	  
In a table, how many employee people are working iN job_id

	SELECT JOB_ID COUNT(*)  FROM EMPLOYEE GROUP BY JOB_ID;
	SELECT JOB_ID, DEPARTMENT_ID COUNT(*)  FROM EMPLOYEE GROUP BY JOB_ID, DEPARTMENT_ID;

